AFRICA’s foremost broadcast station, Lagos Traffic Radio 96.1 FM, will hold its 10th colloquium next week in Lagos. Those expected are Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu, Minister of Works and Housing Babatunde Fashola, Managing Director of Lagos Metropolitan Transport Authority (LAMATA) Mrs. Abimbola Akinajo, and former Commissioner for Transportation Prof. Bamidele Badejo. The colloquium, with its theme: Integrated Transport System as a Lifeline for Economic Growth, is part of the week-long activities to mark the radio station’s 10th year anniversary from May 23 to 29.   Oyo APC leaders back aspirant     APC youths seek 35 per cent inclusion in govt     Petroleum body fires Ondo task force chair   General Manager Tayo Akanle said: “The weeklong felicitation has been designed to reflect on this decade-long adventure… and a glance into opportunities ahead…” A statement by Assistant Director (News and Programmes) Mrs. Adetola Akindele, said National President of Chartered Institute of Logistics and Transport (CILT) Nfon Usoro and Chairman of Air Peace Airlines Allen Onyeama will join Badejo and Akinajo to discuss the theme. Highlights of the anniversary include an advocacy walk on May 23, the colloquium, and a gala and award night.